title: For Sale:  FN SCAR 17S
postcontent: This auction is for a brand new in the box FN Herstal SCAR 17S black. This is the 7.62X51/.308 Winchester, one in twelve twist model. This is the one that will reach out and touch someone. I'll let the stock photos tell the story but I'll just go over the features as she sits here on my lap. The upper receiver has an integral 16" rail. The flip up rear sight is windage and elevation adjustable. It allows you to flip between either of two different apertures. It can be moved forward or back on the upper rail. The flip up front sight is mounted on the gas block and is also windage and elevation adjustable. The post is square in cross section and about 1/16" in width. The elevation adjustment is similar to that of the M16. The 16.25" barrel is free floating; has a cold hammer forged, hardchromed bore; and its muzzle is threaded 5/8" X 24tpi having what I expect to be a flash hider, although it suggests it might function as a brake as well. I couldn't find the answer to that on the FN website. The forearm has three accessory rails. There are ambidextrous integral forward and rear of receiver sling attachment points. They were designed for tactical slings, not traditional high power shooting slings. Shame on them. Oh well, ideas change, eh? There is a bolt hold open reminiscent of the M16. The magazine release is ambidextrous as is the safety/selector. Two positions only....sorry. The buttstock collapses and folds to create an overall length between 28.5" and 38.5". It has an adjustable cheek piece that elevates to fine tune your spot weld/sight picture. I like that because I tend to "crane" forward and take a tight weld which actually puts me low on the iron sights. With the cheek piece up, I get a perfect sight picture when I'm settled in the way I prefer. I'll bet this would be fun to shoot at distance. title: For Sale:  FN SCAR 17S
postcontent: This auction is for a brand new in the box FN Herstal SCAR 17S black. This is the 7.62X51/.308 Winchester, one in twelve twist model. This is the one that will reach out and touch someone. I'll let the stock photos tell the story but I'll just go over the features as she sits here on my lap. The upper receiver has an integral 16" rail. The flip up rear sight is windage and elevation adjustable. It allows you to flip between either of two different apertures. It can be moved forward or back on the upper rail. The flip up front sight is mounted on the gas block and is also windage and elevation adjustable. The post is square in cross section and about 1/16" in width. The elevation adjustment is similar to that of the M16. The 16.25" barrel is free floating; has a cold hammer forged, hardchromed bore; and its muzzle is threaded 5/8" X 24tpi having what I expect to be a flash hider, although it suggests it might function as a brake as well. I couldn't find the answer to that on the FN website. The forearm has three accessory rails. There are ambidextrous integral forward and rear of receiver sling attachment points. They were designed for tactical slings, not traditional high power shooting slings. Shame on them. Oh well, ideas change, eh? There is a bolt hold open reminiscent of the M16. The magazine release is ambidextrous as is the safety/selector. Two positions only....sorry. The buttstock collapses and folds to create an overall length between 28.5" and 38.5". It has an adjustable cheek piece that elevates to fine tune your spot weld/sight picture. I like that because I tend to "crane" forward and take a tight weld which actually puts me low on the iron sights. With the cheek piece up, I get a perfect sight picture when I'm settled in the way I prefer. I'll bet this would be fun to shoot at distance. FN does brag about the long range accuracy, although it doesn't have what one would consider a target trigger. The pull is military heavy. The rifle weighs 8.0 lbs empty. An owner's manual, a lock, and one 20rd magazine are included.

title: For Sale:  Adams Arms AR15 piston kit - Midlength
postcontent:
Brand new in sealed box.
Adams Arms retrofit piston system - convert your mid-length gas barrel into a clean piston system.
Includes everything needed - bolt carrier, piston/rod, gas block and handguards.

Factory Description - 
Kit has everything you need to replace the standard gas system in your AR-15 and convert it to a reliable, positive-cycling, gas piston system. Eliminates venting of hot gases and powder residue into the bolt carrier and receiver for reduced fouling and less wear on the action. Feeds more smoothly, maintenance is easier, and the gun runs cooler, too. Short-stroke piston shaft eliminates concussive gas expansion in the upper receiver for less violent cycling and reduced felt recoil. Easy to adjust for three levels of gas release: normal fire, firing with a suppressor attached, or a single round fired without cycling. Picatinny rail on the gas block provides mounting space for a variety of front sights. Installation requires removal of original gas block, but no permanent alterations to barrel or upper receiver. Remove the piston system at any time and reinstall the original parts. Replacement handguard provides extra internal clearance for piston rod and has internal shield to protect your hand from heat buildup during sustained fire.

This rifle also comes equipped with a forward-mounted scope base that is ideal for electronic sights or other accessories. 

Stock Configuration & Condition: The stock is a light weight one piece black Synthetic stock. This stock only has very light handling marks. The LOP measures approximately 13 ¼” from the front of the trigger to the back of the metal USGI buttplate. The stock rates in about Excellent overall condition. 

Type of Finish: Matte 

Finish Originality: Factory Original 

Bore Condition: The bore is Bright and the rifling is Sharp. There is no apparent erosion. This rifle appears to have never been fired 

Overall Condition: This rifle retains about 99% of its metal finish. The balance of the finish shows very light handling marks. The screw heads are Sharp. The markings are Clear. Overall, this rifle rates in about Excellent condition. 

Mechanics: The action functions correctly. We have not fired this rifle. 

Box, Paperwork & Accessories: Included with this rifle is the technical manual for M1A type riffles, Springfield Armory Instruction manual, and a nice article that was included with the rifle when purchased about the “Mysterious Slam Fire”.
